Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on developing a Keyword Spotting (KWS) system for speech recognition, which falls under the sound category.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper uses Deep Neural Network (DNN) and Connectionist Temporal Classifier (CTC) for speech recognition, which are techniques used in natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning techniques such as DNN and CTC for speech recognition.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses AI techniques such as DNN and CTC for speech recognition.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the implementation of the KWS system on power-constrained small-footprint mobile devices, which falls under the systems and control category.
